results.name: Number of complete planar branching factorizations of n.
comment: A planar branching factorization of n is either the number n itself or a sequence of at least two planar branching factorizations, one of each factor in an ordered factorization of n. A planar branching factorization is complete if the leaves are all prime numbers.
formula: a(product of n distinct primes) = A032037(n).
results.author: _Gus Wiseman_, Sep 11 2018
